cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CL 

This paper is about object detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves training a neural network to extract features and select bounding boxes, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments are conducted on image datasets, which also suggests computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) as likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses natural language processing techniques, such as determinantal point processes, to select bounding boxes, which could also fall under computational linguistics (cs.CL).
